thursday i went to the city with my mom my brother joe annella and his mom. we walked around for a while trying to find tickets to a show and then we endede up seeing RENT again. mike and joe were like ow ow when the girls ass was showing i was like omg i dont no them. soo then at inter mission we thought the guys were just going out to smoke... well it turns out that they went into the bar next door. marie was soooo pissed. but they were drinking with the guy that plays angel in the play after he/she died. i was like lucky. so idk my brother was in a good mood and decided to buy me a signed playbill a signed poster and a picture with the guys that play mark and roger. ok well when we were walking back to the train my brother and joe were singing and rapping in the middle of the street. i was like ahhhhhh!!!! ok so we didnt get back to whiteplains till like 12:30 so then i came home and went to bed. 

friday i hung out with erin!!! ahh i hadnt seen her in like forever!!! we were gunna go out but then we were driving past blockbuster and we decided to have a movie night!!! we rented wimbolton, napolian dynomite and lader 49. when we got home and were ready to watch wimbolton... the wrong movie was in the case. so we were bummed. o well we watched napolian dynomite... gosh haha i <33 that movie... then we didnt wanna watch ladder 49. 

saturday i went to long island to rossavelt feild mall. i was spost to meet shanna there but she couldnt go. instead i spent the whole day shopping with my mom. the best thing about it was that she bought me everything that i wanted. sry i no that sounds spoiled. we spent like 2 hours in hollister. i bought like the whole store. i bought like 10 lacoste shirts, 5 juicy outfits. wow 6 pairs of sneakers and 7 pairs of flip flops. the funny thing is that when we were leaving my mom says well come back here for camp shopping and if you want more spring stuff. i was wow i lovee you!!! well i got home and decided to go on the hollister web site and i got 2 more pairs of flip flops 1 more pair of jeans and 5 more shirts. then i was talking to amanda and we bought bought stuff at urban outfitters. wow i did some major shopping. it was fun.


well today im going to my grandmas house in nj. it should be ok. i dont no how long i cant stand my cousin. all she does is talk. o well.... ill update tommorow prob

wow i havent updated in like forever!!!! well ill start with last weekend....

friday 4th- well it was the winter ball at harvey!!! i had amazing time!!! there werent that many people there but i think it was better that way. it was me yulia, marlie, rachael, gretel, katie, lauren, emma l, emma s, austin, maranda, grant, dylan, mouse, matt, david, ali walkup, scott, joe, seafeld, aaron, doni, alex, marille, josh, reed, there was more  people but i dont no there names. well we had a amazing time getting all dressed up and everything. there was tons of dancing even though the DJ sucked!!! he was the nurses son and lets just say that he did it for free. well after the dance yulia slept over. we watched the grudge and were drinking. IT WAS HER FIRST TIME EVER DRINKING!!!! ahh it was sooo funny, but i guess you had to be there.

saturday 5th- we went into harrison to get yulias nails done and then we hung out with jessica alsina for the afternoon. it was fun because i havent seen jessica for like 3 years. then me and yulia went back to my house to play tennis and then her mom came. we had a fun day!!! then after yulia left i went to the movies with leydi. we didnt end up seeing anything. we got coffee and then just hung out in whiteplains.

sunday 6th- i had a swim meet that day so it kinda took up the whole day and then i just passed out.

monday- didnt go to school cause i was sick.

tuesday- didnt go to school cause i had to swim

wensday- i went to school and i fuckin couldnt take all the drama!!!! so instead of going to brittanys house just to hear her talk about all the other fuckin drama i came home.

thursday- didnt go to school cause i had more swimming.

friday- didnt go to school cause u never go the last day before a vacation.

friday night - my mom decided that we werent spending enough time with each other so she decided to make friday and saturday a day with her. so firday she made me go to this scrapbook class/ party with her. like i made a scrapbook of my dog but i hated going there and wasting my time!!! we didnt get home till like 1:30 in the morning!!! ugh lets hope i never have to do that again!!!

saturday- well i had softball practice in the morning and then my mom made me go to the play with her. the only bad thing was that my friend had bought tickets for sunday. so i went both days. it was amazing!!!! they did a great job!!! after the show on sunday i got to see people that i dont really get to see any more like natalia ashley ryan ANDREW hahaha eww andrew dressler!!! also like amanda angalia brook chelsea and other people were there.... it was cool seeing every1!!! sometimes i miss harrison.

 

well now i have 2 weeks of vacation!!!! and nothing to do!! since my brother doesnt have off i cant go anywhere... it sux major ass!!! well im gunna hang out with my harvey friends this week and maybe visit hhs once and me and amanda are gunna go to lmk... so it will be funn!!!

 

p.s. sry its kinda long

tonight has been the worst night ever!!!! brittany stood me up because she tought that i called her a whore... thanks to rachael who told her!!! by the way it isnt true!!! i dont need this right now!!! ive been crying over this all day!!! i dont even fuckin no y!!! im not gunna waste  my time with people like this!!! y would i think that after my dad died my friends would have my back??? that was the fuckin stupidest thing i could have done!!! i dont need people like that in my life!!!

tuesday school... yeah well nothing special

You Know You're From Westchester When...
You go to a Dave Matthews Band concert and end up running into people you know from your school. Half the people in your school mysteriously develop inner-Queens accents during 7th and 8th grade. Starbucks is a regular stop for you. You say Abercrombie & Fitch makes you want to puke, yet you sport at least one outfit from the store each week NYU is your top choice for college. If you go to Catholic school, you know everyone at all the Catholic schools in Westchester. If you go to public school you still manage to know everyone at all the Catholic schools in Westchester. Below 1400 is a "so-so" SAT score You claim to hate your school, but you go to all the dances and play at least one varsity sport anyway. Even though your best friend lives a stone's throw away, you have most of your conversations with him/her on AOL or AIM. You know you have to act tough when going to The Galleria, or else you might get shot. You know you have to act sophisticated when you go to The Westchester, or else you'll get kicked out. Your summer vacation is most likely one of the following: LBI, Cape May, Wildwood, Seaside Heights, or, more simply "The Jersey Shore." You know someone who knows the girl who starred in "The Blair Witch Project." Your dad works in an office and wears a suit and tie to work every day. Your mom either works part-time or volunteers, but whatever she does, it's enough to hold a 24-hour a day guilt-trip over you. If you don't drive, the Metro North train is your best friend, assuming, of course, you're able to avoid the ticket-collector. A trip into NYC for a day is your idea of "getting away from it all." It pisses you off that your friends from the Bronx call this area "upstate New York." You've met Vanessa Williams at least once. You complain that the Jefferson Valley Mall is trash, but you find yourself hanging out there every weekend anyway. You think anyone who lives south of New Jersey is a hick. Everyone winds up spending Spring Break in the Hamptons. The students in your school drive nicer cars than the teachers.
